@startuml NeuroScreen-A EEG Upload Flow
!define PRIMARYCOLOR #FF6B6B
!define SECONDARYCOLOR #4ECDC4
!define TERTIARYCOLOR #45B7D1

title NeuroScreen-A: Flujo de Procesamiento de Carga EEG\nDesde Upload hasta Resultado de Predicción

participant "👤 Usuario\n(Cliente Web)" as USER
participant "🌐 React Frontend\n(Browser)" as BROWSER
participant "🔧 API Flask\n(Gunicorn)" as API
participant "📊 Redis\n(Celery Broker)" as REDIS
participant "⚙️ Worker\n(Celery)" as WORKER
participant "🗄️ PostgreSQL\n(Base Datos)" as DB
participant "🧠 ML Pipeline\n(Preprocessing)" as ML_PREP
participant "🤖 ML Pipeline\n(Inference)" as ML_INFER
participant "📈 Visualization\n(Async)" as VIZ

== FASE 1: UPLOAD ==

USER -> BROWSER: Selecciona archivo EEG\n+ patient_id
note right of USER
  Archivo: .edf, .csv, .parquet, .json
  Max: 500 MB (Config.EEG_MAX_FILE_SIZE_BYTES)
end note

BROWSER -> API: POST /eeg-records/upload\n[multipart/form-data]\nfile + patient_id + JWT
note over API
  1. Valida JWT token
  2. Verifica patient_id existe
  3. Valida extensión y tamaño
end note

API -> API: Guarda archivo temporal\n(temp_{uuid}.ext)

API -> API: EegReaderFactory.get_reader()\n→ retorna reader específico para formato

API -> API: reader.read(temp_path)\n→ DataFrame con columnas validadas

API -> API: Convierte a Parquet\n(optimizado, columnar)

API -> API: Elimina archivo temporal

API -> DB: INSERT INTO eeg_records\n(patient_id, uploader_id, file_path,\nfile_type, file_size_bytes,\nstatus=PENDING, created_at)

API -> REDIS: Celery.delay(process_eeg_record)\nEnqueue task: {eeg_record_id}
note over API
  Envía mensaje JSON a Redis queue
  TTL: configurable (default 24h)
end note

API -> BROWSER: 202 Accepted\n{id, status: 'pending', patient_id}

BROWSER -> USER: Muestra UI: "Procesando...\nEspere mientras se analiza"
note right of USER
  Frontend entra en polling loop:
  GET /eeg-records/{id}/status c/2s
end note

== FASE 2: PROCESAMIENTO ASINCRÓNICO ==

REDIS -> WORKER: Dequeue task: process_eeg_record(eeg_record_id)
note over WORKER
  Worker obtiene task del broker Redis
  Timeout: 120s (configurable)
end note

WORKER -> DB: SELECT EegRecord WHERE id=eeg_record_id

DB -> WORKER: Retorna registro\n(status=PENDING)

WORKER -> DB: UPDATE eeg_records\nSET status=PROCESSING

WORKER -> ML_PREP: build_tensor_from_parquet(\nparquet_path, win_size=256,\nstep_size=256, use_bands=True)

ML_PREP -> ML_PREP: Lee archivo Parquet\n(optimizado en memoria)

ML_PREP -> ML_PREP: Valida canales requeridos\n(verifica CHANNELS en config)
note over ML_PREP
  Requeridos: 64 canales EEG
  Si faltan: lanza ValueError
  Si presentes: continúa
end note

ML_PREP -> ML_PREP: Para cada trial en archivo:\n1. Extrae ventanas (win_size=256)\n2. Para cada canal:\n   a. get_channel_signal()\n   b. extract_frequency_bands():\n      - raw\n      - delta (0.5-4 Hz)\n      - theta (4-8 Hz)\n      - alpha (8-13 Hz)\n      - beta (13-30 Hz)\n      - gamma (30-50 Hz)\n   c. normalize_signal() → Z-score\n3. Construye matriz 4D:\n   shape = (N_samples, 64*6, 256, 1)

ML_PREP -> WORKER: Retorna tensor X\n(N_samples, 384, 256, 1) float32

WORKER -> ML_INFER: run_inference(X)\n→ carga modelo + predicción

ML_INFER -> ML_INFER: Load eegnet_model.keras\nfrom /app/dl_models/

ML_INFER -> ML_INFER: Batch prediction:\nfor sample in X:\n  logits = model(sample)\n  prob = sigmoid(logits)\n  confidence = max(prob)

ML_INFER -> ML_INFER: Agregación:\nlabel = majority_vote(predicciones)\nraw_prob = mean(probabilities)

ML_INFER -> WORKER: Retorna (label, raw_prob, confidence)\nEj: ('alcohol', 0.87, 0.92)

WORKER -> DB: INSERT INTO prediction_results\n(eeg_record_id, result, confidence,\nraw_probability, model_version='eegnet_v1')

DB -> WORKER: Retorna prediction.id

WORKER -> DB: INSERT INTO prediction_visualizations\n(prediction_id, status='pending')

WORKER -> DB: UPDATE eeg_records\nSET status=PROCESSED,\nprocessing_time_ms=4320,\nerror_msg=NULL

WORKER -> REDIS: Celery.delay(generate_eeg_visualizations)\nEnqueue subtask: {eeg_record_id, prediction_id}
note over WORKER
  Encadena tarea async de visualización
  No espera su resultado (fire-and-forget)
end note

WORKER -> WORKER: Log success\n@audit.logged action='infer',\ndetails={...}

== FASE 3: POLLING DEL CLIENTE ==

BROWSER -> API: GET /eeg-records/{id}/status\n[cada 2 segundos]

API -> DB: SELECT status, processing_time_ms\nFROM eeg_records

DB -> API: {status: 'PROCESSED', processing_time_ms: 4320}

API -> BROWSER: 200 OK\n{status: 'processed', time_ms: 4320}

BROWSER -> USER: Actualiza UI:\n"✓ Predicción generada\nEsperando visualizaciones..."

== FASE 4: GENERACIÓN DE VISUALIZACIONES ==

REDIS -> WORKER: Dequeue generate_eeg_visualizations(eeg_record_id, prediction_id)

WORKER -> DB: SELECT prediction_visualizations\nWHERE prediction_id=prediction_id

WORKER -> DB: UPDATE prediction_visualizations\nSET status='processing'

WORKER -> VIZ: generate_waveforms(\nparquet_path, trial_index=0, win_size=256)

VIZ -> VIZ: Lee parquet (directo, sin re-tensorizar)\nExtrae raw waveforms por canal\nFormatea JSON con timestamps

VIZ -> WORKER: Retorna {channels: {...}, timestamps: [...]}

WORKER -> ML_PREP: build_tensor_from_parquet()\n(necesario para calcular importancia)

ML_PREP -> WORKER: Retorna tensor X

WORKER -> VIZ: generate_channel_importance(X)\n→ calcula importancia de cada canal\n(attention/gradient-based)

VIZ -> WORKER: Retorna {ch_names: [...], scores: [...]}

WORKER -> VIZ: generate_topomap(importance)\n→ mapeo espacial 2D de importancia

VIZ -> WORKER: Retorna {x: [...], y: [...], values: [...]}

WORKER -> DB: UPDATE prediction_visualizations\nSET waveforms_data={...},\nchannel_importance_data={...},\ntopomap_data={...},\nstatus='completed'

WORKER -> WORKER: Log visualization success

== FASE 5: CLIENTE OBTIENE RESULTADO ==

BROWSER -> API: GET /eeg-records/{id}/visualizations\n?types=waveforms,topomap,channel_importance

API -> DB: SELECT prediction_visualizations\nWHERE prediction_id IN (...)\nAND status='completed'

DB -> API: Retorna {waveforms_data, topomap_data, channel_importance_data}

API -> BROWSER: 200 OK\n{status: 'completed',\nwaveforms: {...},\ntopomap: {...},\nchannel_importance: {...}}

BROWSER -> USER: Renderiza resultados:\n- Gráfico de ondas EEG\n- Topomap con importancia\n- Predicción: "ALCOHOLISMO" (87%)

USER -> USER: ✓ Análisis completado

== MANEJO DE ERRORES ==

note over WORKER
  Si error en process_eeg_record():
  1. Rollback de cambios parciales
  2. UPDATE eeg_record status=FAILED
  3. INSERT error_msg (limpio a 500 chars)
  4. Reintentos: max_retries=3, countdown=30s
  5. @audit.logged action='infer', status='failed'
  
  Si error en visualizations:
  1. UPDATE status='failed', error_msg=str(e)
  2. Rollback transacción
  3. No afecta prediction guardada
  4. Usuario puede descargar resultado sin viz
end note

note over DB
  Transacciones ACID:
  - Serialization: REPEATABLE READ
  - Rollback automático si error
  - Soft delete (is_deleted flag)
  - FK constraints activos
end note

== TIMELINES Y TIMEOUTS ==

note right of API
  **Upload Phase (SÍNCRONO):**
  - Validación: 100-500ms
  - Conversión a parquet: 1-5s
  - INSERT BD: 50-200ms
  - Total: <10s
  - Retorna 202 inmediatamente
end note

note right of WORKER
  **Processing Phase (ASINCRÓNICO):**
  - Lectura parquet: 1-2s
  - Preprocessing: 2-5s
  - Inference: 3-10s
  - Insert BD: 100-500ms
  - **Total: 6-18s**
  - Timeout: 120s (configurable)
end note

note right of VIZ
  **Visualization Phase:**
  - Waveform generation: 1-3s
  - Importancia calculation: 2-5s
  - Topomap rendering: 1-2s
  - **Total: 4-10s**
  - Timeout: 120s
end note

note right of BROWSER
  **Cliente Polling:**
  - Intervalo: cada 2000ms
  - Max intentos: 300 (10 minutos)
  - Backoff exponencial: 2s → 5s
  - WebSocket fallback (si implementado)
end note

@enduml
